<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,585,899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">
Two specimens, one male and one female, were found with corresponding data matching the original description which referred to “one pair”. A small label reading “Type” was added to the male specimen by the NHM. We here designate the male specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[384,482,731,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">lectotype</typeStatus>
and female specimen as the 
<typeStatus box="[787,934,731,755]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">paralectotype</typeStatus>
. Labels for the designated male specimen read: “Type” “Cordova” “ 
<collectingCountry box="[367,453,767,791]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Mexico</collectingCountry>
./Salle Coll.” “B.C.A. Col. II (1)./ 
<taxonomicName box="[802,946,767,791]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Carpophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carpophilus</taxonomicName>
”. A red label is added with the following text: “ 
<typeStatus box="[160,315,803,827]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">LECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharp" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1889" box="[323,609,803,827]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Carpophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassus">Carpophilus crassus Sharp</taxonomicName>
/Desig. By/Powell and Martin 2019”. For the female, labels read: “Cordova” “ 
<collectingCountry box="[161,247,839,863]" name="Mexico" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">Mexico</collectingCountry>
./Salle Coll.” “B.C.A. Col. 
<date box="[539,584,839,863]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">II. 1.</date>
/ 
<taxonomicName box="[591,727,839,863]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Carpophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Carpophilus</taxonomicName>
/crassus,/Sharp” “Type”. A label is added with the following text: “ 
<typeStatus box="[160,385,875,899]" pageId="3" pageNumber="300">PARALECTOTYPE</typeStatus>
/ 
<taxonomicName authority="Sharp" authorityName="Sharp" authorityYear="1889" box="[393,676,875,899]" class="Insecta" family="Nitidulidae" genus="Carpophilus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="300" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="crassus">Carpophilus crassus Sharp</taxonomicName>
